      <scopecontent>
         <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
         <p>This Civil War collection consists of requisitions and
         receipts (20 items) issued primarily by Capt. William Miller,
         Assistant Quartermaster serving on the staff Col. Turner
         Ashby's 7th Virginia Cavalry Regiment, Confederate States
         Army. The documents date from the period Dec. 1861-March 1862
         and many bear Ashby's signature. Included are receipts for
         corn, oats, and hay purchased from various farmers.</p>
      </scopecontent>
